Todo Application Project
Project Overview
Build a Todo application using React that showcases your frontend engineering skills. You’ll demonstrate your ability to work with APIs, implement React patterns, handle routing, and create accessible user interfaces.

Technology Stack
Required:

React 19+ (functional components and hooks), with Suspense and ErrorBoundary and Proper SEO.
React Router or Tanstack Router
API integration (fetch or axios with Tanstack Query or swr)
One consistent styling approach: Tailwind CSS (recommended), CSS Modules, Styled Components, or vanilla CSS with BEM
Suggested Libraries:

UI: ShadCN/UI (recommended), Chakra UI, React-Aria, or Daisy UI
Icons: React Icons, Lucide React, or Iconify
Forms: Tanstack Form or React Hook Form
API Details
Detail Value
Base URL https://api.oluwasetemi.dev
Documentation https://api.oluwasetemi.dev/reference
Core Endpoints:

GET /todos – List all todos
GET /todos/{id} – Get a single todo
POST /todos – Create a todo
PUT /todos/{id} – Update a todo
DELETE /todos/{id} – Delete a todo
For Advanced Features:

Authentication: /auth/register, /auth/login, /auth/me, /auth/logout
WebSocket: WS /ws/tasks for real-time updates
Required Features (50%)
Todo List & Pagination
Display todos from the API with pagination (10 items per page)
Show title, completion status, and other relevant information
Include user-friendly pagination controls
Todo Details
Create a nested route to display individual todo details
Show all available information about the selected item
Include navigation back to the main list
Error Handling
Implement Error Boundary component
Add a test route that triggers the error boundary
Create a custom 404 page for undefined routes
Basic UI/UX
Use semantic HTML and proper accessibility attributes
Ensure mobile and desktop responsiveness
Maintain consistent styling
Show loading states during API calls
Search & Filtering
Add search functionality to filter todos by title
Implement filters for completion status (all/complete/incomplete)
Bonus Features
Implement any of these for extra credit:

CRUD Operations

Create: Add new todos with a form/modal
Update: Edit existing todos
Delete: Remove todos with confirmation dialog
Authentication & User Management

Create signup and login flows with validation
Show only the logged-in user’s tasks
Add protected routes
Create a simple user profile page
Real-Time Notifications

Connect to WebSocket API for live updates
Show notifications when tasks change
Add visual indicators for updates
Create a notifications center
Offline Capabilities

Cache API responses.
Implement offline support
